By Olawale Ayeni, Abuja Ahead of the start of Nigeria National League (NNL) 2020/21 season, the president of Oyah sports FC of Suleja in Niger state, Osman Sillah has said that his team would not leave any stone unturned in their quest to gain promotion to the Nigerian Professional Football League (NPFL). Osman, the Sierra Leone born administrator whom football business lured to Nigeria while speaking in an online interview on Sports World WhatsApp platform said the club home ground has been renovated ahead of the start of the NNL season.  “I have invested millions of Naira in renovating the stadium in Suleja with an understanding with the authorities in the local government.”  ” My ultimate goal is to see Oyah sports getting a promotion slot to the NPFL with a standard facility to play in and presenting a model club that will be every fan’s delight”.  The very experienced football scout turned administrator also revealed that his first club Royal Stars in Sierra Leone are now in partnership with Oyah sports for movement of players between both clubs which will yield fruitful results. He further explained that a lot of players from Nigeria’ has benefited from his various links abroad.